# Personal Command Center

> Your private space for capturing thoughts, queuing prompts for Claude, and parking ideas until they're ready to become projects.

---

## How to Add Content (All Files Work the Same Way)

Every Personal document follows the same two-step pattern:

### Step 1: Copy the Template
At the top of each file, you'll find a template in a code block. Copy it.

### Step 2: Paste in the Designated Area
Scroll down until you see the big box that says **"YOUR [X] GO HERE"**. Paste your content there.

```
╔═══════════════════════════════════════╗
║       YOUR [X] GO HERE                ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════╝

<-- Paste here, between the START and END boxes -->

╔═══════════════════════════════════════╗
║     END OF YOUR [X] SECTION           ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════╝
```

**Everything above the START box** = Instructions and templates (don't edit)
**Everything between the boxes** = YOUR content goes here
**Everything below the END box** = Reference material (don't edit)

