## Workflow Overview

```
Capture → Process → Act → Archive
```

1. **Capture** — Quick-dump thoughts, prompts, ideas without friction
2. **Process** — Claude reads and triages during sessions
3. **Act** — Items become plans, research, or implementations
4. **Archive** — Completed items move to Archive/ folder monthly

---

## What Each Document Is For

### [[Personal/Thoughts|Thoughts.md]]
**Purpose:** Stream of consciousness capture

Write anything here — observations, questions, half-formed ideas, things you're stuck on. No format required. Claude will read these and either act on them, ask clarifying questions, or acknowledge them.

### [[Personal/Prompts|Prompts.md]]
**Purpose:** Queued instructions for Claude to execute

When you want Claude to do something specific, queue it here. Each prompt has a priority (P0-P3) and status (pending/completed). Claude processes these in priority order and marks them complete when done.

**Important:** All prompt instructions start with `/start-task` for intelligent routing.

### [[Personal/Ideas|Ideas.md]]
**Purpose:** Parking lot for future work

Ideas that aren't ready for action yet. Park them here, categorize them (feature/project/experiment/tool/content/business), and review periodically. Good ideas get promoted to Projects; bad ideas get discarded.

### [[Personal/Learning|Learning.md]]
**Purpose:** Insights and lessons learned

Document what you learn as you work. Multiple entry types: insights (💡), mistakes (⚠️), successes (✅), techniques (🔧). Reference these during similar work later.

### [[Personal/Decisions|Decisions.md]]
**Purpose:** Quick decisions log

For small decisions that matter but don't need full Architecture Decision Records. Document what you decided, why, and what alternatives you rejected. Useful for "why did I do X?" moments.

